00:03:40.190 --> 00:03:42.880
So what can public health
do about these challenges?

00:03:42.880 --> 00:03:45.580
How can public health help?

00:03:45.580 --> 00:03:48.580
Let me offer a few
examples to illustrate

00:03:48.580 --> 00:03:50.890
how public health can help.

00:03:50.890 --> 00:03:55.750
We can recognize that healthy
lives across the life course

00:03:55.750 --> 00:04:00.490
are not just those lived
without sickness and disability.

00:04:00.490 --> 00:04:04.930
We can help people engage in
wellness across their life

00:04:04.930 --> 00:04:06.190
spans.

00:04:06.190 --> 00:04:07.910
What do we mean by that?

00:04:07.910 --> 00:04:10.990
We can help people
by easing access

00:04:10.990 --> 00:04:14.320
to affordable and
nutritious food.

00:04:14.320 --> 00:04:19.329
We can help by promoting
social connectedness.

00:04:19.329 --> 00:04:25.810
We can help by offering access
to good quality health care,

00:04:25.810 --> 00:04:29.080
and we can help by
educating people

00:04:29.080 --> 00:04:32.350
about the importance
of managing stress

00:04:32.350 --> 00:04:36.340
and getting enough
sleep and exercise.

00:04:36.340 --> 00:04:39.850
We can also encourage
an holistic approach

00:04:39.850 --> 00:04:44.290
that supports these
foundations with respect

00:04:44.290 --> 00:04:50.110
to personal health, as well
as within healthy communities.

00:04:50.110 --> 00:04:53.050
And perhaps most
importantly, we can

00:04:53.050 --> 00:04:56.620
help to bring evidence
that drives policy

00:04:56.620 --> 00:05:00.160
to promote systems
and approaches that

00:05:00.160 --> 00:05:05.080
bolster the well-being
of entire populations.

00:05:05.080 --> 00:05:07.060
We here at the
Harvard Chan School

00:05:07.060 --> 00:05:10.870
consider well-being as
such an important part

00:05:10.870 --> 00:05:16.030
of what constitutes a healthy
world that we have identified

00:05:16.030 --> 00:05:20.200
well-being and nutrition as
key components of our research

00:05:20.200 --> 00:05:22.240
mission.

