00:06:51.385 --> 00:06:54.910
I'm very honored,
privileged, and always

00:06:54.910 --> 00:06:57.850
happy to come back to Boston.

00:06:57.850 --> 00:07:02.920
My training was here in internal
medicine, endocrinology,

00:07:02.920 --> 00:07:04.670
and then neuroendocrinology.

00:07:04.670 --> 00:07:09.920
So I was telling Dean Williams
that my career has spanned

00:07:09.920 --> 00:07:12.640
internal medicine,
endocrinology,

00:07:12.640 --> 00:07:16.690
discovery of neuropeptides
as molecules of emotion,

00:07:16.690 --> 00:07:20.380
getting into mind-body
medicine, integrative health,

00:07:20.380 --> 00:07:24.220
and well-being, and today,
addressing the hard problem

00:07:24.220 --> 00:07:26.300
of consciousness.

00:07:26.300 --> 00:07:29.110
So I'd like to
start off by saying

00:07:29.110 --> 00:07:36.220
that as biological organisms, we
are already a holistic process.

00:07:36.220 --> 00:07:40.350
All biological organisms
function holistically.

00:07:40.350 --> 00:07:44.620
The human body has more
than 60 trillion cells,

00:07:44.620 --> 00:07:48.460
which is more than all the
stars in the Milky Way galaxy.

00:07:48.460 --> 00:07:51.820
A human body can think
thoughts, play a piano,

00:07:51.820 --> 00:07:56.550
kill germs, remove toxins, make
a baby all at the same time,

00:07:56.550 --> 00:08:01.510
while monitoring the
movement of planets and stars

00:08:01.510 --> 00:08:04.870
as its own biological
rhythm-- circadian rhythms,

00:08:04.870 --> 00:08:10.330
seasonal rhythms, gravitational
rhythms, even lunar rhythms.

00:08:10.330 --> 00:08:14.020
That homeostasis,
or self-regulation,

00:08:14.020 --> 00:08:16.030
is our natural state.

00:08:16.030 --> 00:08:20.050
And the extreme end
of the spectrum--

00:08:20.050 --> 00:08:22.330
if homeostasis of
self-regulation, which

00:08:22.330 --> 00:08:27.540
is a dynamic process of
non-change within change

00:08:27.540 --> 00:08:32.169
is one extreme, then
low-grade chronic inflammation

00:08:32.169 --> 00:08:38.650
is the other extreme,
which leads to disease.

00:08:38.650 --> 00:08:44.020
Only 5%-- only 5% of
disease-related gene mutations

00:08:44.020 --> 00:08:48.740
are fully penetrant, which
means they cannot be stopped.

00:08:48.740 --> 00:08:49.840
5%.

00:08:49.840 --> 00:08:53.180
If somebody has a BRCA gene,
for example, for breast cancer,

00:08:53.180 --> 00:08:55.690
that's a fully-penetrant gene.

00:08:55.690 --> 00:09:00.920
And one needs to do remedial
measures as prevention.

00:09:00.920 --> 00:09:06.460
Angelina Jolie has gone public
with her preventive mastectomy

00:09:06.460 --> 00:09:09.110
and so forth, because
she had that gene.

00:09:09.110 --> 00:09:11.380
Now, what most
people don't know,

00:09:11.380 --> 00:09:14.350
other than those who
are really involved,

00:09:14.350 --> 00:09:20.260
is that's true of 95% of
chronic illness in our world.

00:09:20.260 --> 00:09:23.920
Even mutations that
lead to disease

00:09:23.920 --> 00:09:25.280
are not fully penetrant.

00:09:25.280 --> 00:09:28.840
So if you have,
say, 30 identified

00:09:28.840 --> 00:09:33.280
genes for Alzheimer's, only
three are fully penetrant.

00:09:33.280 --> 00:09:37.090
Hundreds of genes are involved
in various types of cancer.

00:09:37.090 --> 00:09:40.270
Less than 5% are
fully penetrant.

00:09:40.270 --> 00:09:43.780
And the fact that
the risk factors

00:09:43.780 --> 00:09:48.220
for heart disease,
stroke, inflammation,

00:09:48.220 --> 00:09:53.300
cancer autoimmune illness,
infectious diseases

00:09:53.300 --> 00:09:56.860
are actually common, they're
the same risk factors

00:09:56.860 --> 00:10:00.550
that we've been looking at
for cardiovascular disease

00:10:00.550 --> 00:10:02.960
for the last 35 years.

00:10:02.960 --> 00:10:08.720
So with that understanding of
our body as a holistic process,

00:10:08.720 --> 00:10:10.750
a body as a verb--

00:10:10.750 --> 00:10:15.380
and I'd like to say that nouns
are conventions of language,

00:10:15.380 --> 00:10:17.830
but they do not reflect reality.

00:10:17.830 --> 00:10:20.700
Reality is always an activity.

00:10:20.700 --> 00:10:22.630
A body is an activity.

00:10:22.630 --> 00:10:26.650
Even this is an activity at the
level of atoms and particles.

00:10:26.650 --> 00:10:31.250
But biological organisms are
so dynamic at maintaining

00:10:31.250 --> 00:10:35.680
self-regulation that if we put
attention to just a few things,

00:10:35.680 --> 00:10:40.270
so the neural sciences
of neuroplasticity--

00:10:40.270 --> 00:10:44.080
neuroplasticity means that
your conscious choices

00:10:44.080 --> 00:10:46.180
regulate your neural networks.

00:10:46.180 --> 00:10:47.710
And if you make
something a habit,

00:10:47.710 --> 00:10:51.460
you create something called
long-term potentiation

00:10:51.460 --> 00:10:55.070
of neural networks
that basically

00:10:55.070 --> 00:10:59.070
help to regulate
your own biology,

00:10:59.070 --> 00:11:01.910
and so neural feedback,
cardiac feedback.

00:11:01.910 --> 00:11:06.110
But just simple
things like meditation

00:11:06.110 --> 00:11:12.290
will change the way you look
at self-regulation and healing.

00:11:12.290 --> 00:11:14.750
The word "healing" comes
from the word "holy."

00:11:14.750 --> 00:11:19.330
Healing, holy, wholeness,
health are the same word.

00:11:19.330 --> 00:11:24.020
It's reminding yourself of
your connection to wholeness.

00:11:24.020 --> 00:11:28.020
So with what we know of
neuroplasticity, epigenetics,

00:11:28.020 --> 00:11:29.450
which means we--

00:11:29.450 --> 00:11:31.849
every experience that you
have-- every experience,

00:11:31.849 --> 00:11:33.890
including the experience
you're having right now,

00:11:33.890 --> 00:11:37.370
even if you're online and
watching it from India--

00:11:37.370 --> 00:11:42.260
every experience is modulating
not only your neural networks

00:11:42.260 --> 00:11:44.660
but your gene activity.

00:11:44.660 --> 00:11:48.070
And similarly, your
microbiome, which

00:11:48.070 --> 00:11:51.890
is two million extra genes, is
responding to every experience

00:11:51.890 --> 00:11:57.200
you have, whether it's sleep or
food or exercise or meditation

00:11:57.200 --> 00:11:58.820
or yoga.

00:11:58.820 --> 00:12:01.310
So over the years,
I've identified

00:12:01.310 --> 00:12:04.850
what I call the six
pillars of well-being.

00:12:04.850 --> 00:12:10.660
These are not necessarily
in order of importance.

00:12:10.660 --> 00:12:11.910
They're all equally important.

00:12:11.910 --> 00:12:14.240
So the first is sleep.

00:12:14.240 --> 00:12:17.270
We can go into details
at any time on that.

00:12:17.270 --> 00:12:21.410
Second is stress management--
mindfulness, meditation,

00:12:21.410 --> 00:12:25.310
and many other
contemplative techniques

00:12:25.310 --> 00:12:29.240
that have been part of wisdom
traditions all over the world.

00:12:29.240 --> 00:12:31.940
And we have now
original research

00:12:31.940 --> 00:12:34.760
to show that even
a week of practice

00:12:34.760 --> 00:12:39.380
of mindfulness and meditation
will up-regulate your gene

00:12:39.380 --> 00:12:39.980
activity.

00:12:39.980 --> 00:12:43.100
Some genes will go up 17-fold--

00:12:43.100 --> 00:12:46.800
genes for wound healing,
genes for homeostasis.

00:12:46.800 --> 00:12:50.660
And genes that are responsible
for inappropriate inflammation

00:12:50.660 --> 00:12:52.400
will go down.

00:12:52.400 --> 00:12:55.580
We have shown that
telomerase, the enzyme that

00:12:55.580 --> 00:12:59.090
regulates your genetic
clock, in some cases,

00:12:59.090 --> 00:13:03.380
will go up by 40% in people
who practice contemplative

00:13:03.380 --> 00:13:05.870
self-inquiry, mindfulness,
and meditation.

00:13:05.870 --> 00:13:07.950
There's no drug
that will do that.

00:13:07.950 --> 00:13:09.230
So that's the second pillar.

00:13:09.230 --> 00:13:11.610
The third is movement.

00:13:11.610 --> 00:13:14.600
And if you add to that
practices, like yoga

00:13:14.600 --> 00:13:17.060
and breathing prana
and practices,

00:13:17.060 --> 00:13:21.440
you can specifically target
several different organs

00:13:21.440 --> 00:13:22.080
in your body.

00:13:22.080 --> 00:13:26.840
Because yoga has the knowledge
of which visceral nerves are

00:13:26.840 --> 00:13:29.390
activated with which
kind of movement-- yoga

00:13:29.390 --> 00:13:31.840
postures, or asanas,
as they're called.

00:13:31.840 --> 00:13:34.460
So movement is the third pillar.

00:13:34.460 --> 00:13:36.350
The fourth pillar is emotions.

00:13:36.350 --> 00:13:42.350
So we know that stress,
and anger, and hostility,

00:13:42.350 --> 00:13:47.150
and guilt, and shame,
and depression all

00:13:47.150 --> 00:13:51.370
aggravate inflammation,
and raise blood pressure,

00:13:51.370 --> 00:13:54.830
and cause sticky platelets,
and everything that goes wrong

00:13:54.830 --> 00:13:58.290
when homeostasis is disrupted.

00:13:58.290 --> 00:14:02.600
But we now also have evidence
that love, compassion, joy,

00:14:02.600 --> 00:14:08.360
equanimity, a peaceful mind, and
even keeping a gratitude list

00:14:08.360 --> 00:14:10.880
will decrease
inflammatory markers

00:14:10.880 --> 00:14:15.290
and activate the genes that
are responsible for homeostasis

00:14:15.290 --> 00:14:17.150
and self-regulation.

00:14:17.150 --> 00:14:23.360
So emotions become very
practical as a way to harness

00:14:23.360 --> 00:14:26.330
emotional and
social intelligence

00:14:26.330 --> 00:14:29.090
for optimal self-regulation.

00:14:29.090 --> 00:14:33.770
And finally, two more things,
which one is nutrition--

00:14:33.770 --> 00:14:35.300
Michelle mentioned.

00:14:35.300 --> 00:14:37.380
When I was training
in internal medicine,

00:14:37.380 --> 00:14:40.890
people called me and said,
you know, I changed my diet,

00:14:40.890 --> 00:14:44.884
and my arthritis went away,
or my asthma went away.

00:14:44.884 --> 00:14:45.800
I didn't believe them.

00:14:45.800 --> 00:14:48.820
I had no basis to understand
how that happened.

00:14:48.820 --> 00:14:52.940
But now that we know that the
microbiome, two million genes

00:14:52.940 --> 00:14:56.090
in your gut, the first
thing they see is food.

00:14:56.090 --> 00:14:58.150
And if your food
is contaminated,

00:14:58.150 --> 00:15:02.000
has too much fat, too much
sugar, too many chemicals,

00:15:02.000 --> 00:15:05.960
or pesticides, or petroleum
products, or processed food,

00:15:05.960 --> 00:15:10.940
then you have dysbiosis,
inflamed microbiome that causes

00:15:10.940 --> 00:15:12.300
inflammation in the body.

00:15:12.300 --> 00:15:17.210
Your microbiome, your genes,
and your epigenetic mechanisms

00:15:17.210 --> 00:15:19.130
are all influences--

00:15:19.130 --> 00:15:22.820
the metabolic activity
in your body right now.

00:15:22.820 --> 00:15:25.050
So nutrition becomes
very important.

00:15:25.050 --> 00:15:28.790
And then, Carol was asking
me, I think, earlier,

00:15:28.790 --> 00:15:32.840
do I experience jet lag
because I travel so much?

00:15:32.840 --> 00:15:34.970
And I think this is a
very important point,

00:15:34.970 --> 00:15:36.680
that our biological
rhythms are very

00:15:36.680 --> 00:15:39.010
important in self-regulation.

00:15:39.010 --> 00:15:43.700
And so that we now know that
if you eat within the eight

00:15:43.700 --> 00:15:49.080
hours of daylight, if you
get good sleep at night,

00:15:49.080 --> 00:15:52.520
and if you ground yourself,
even by touching a tree

00:15:52.520 --> 00:15:55.090
or walking barefoot
on the earth,

00:15:55.090 --> 00:16:01.190
or on grass, or on the beach, or
even using a grounding device,

00:16:01.190 --> 00:16:04.060
that will decrease
inflammation in your body,

00:16:04.060 --> 00:16:09.340
avoid disruption of
circadian rhythms, which

00:16:09.340 --> 00:16:11.750
is what jet lag is all about.

00:16:11.750 --> 00:16:14.350
So with these six
pillars that I mentioned,

00:16:14.350 --> 00:16:19.300
you can hone in on your
biological sustainability.

00:16:19.300 --> 00:16:21.670
But if you want to go
beyond that to what,

00:16:21.670 --> 00:16:25.460
essentially, is the mission of
the School of Public Health,

00:16:25.460 --> 00:16:28.210
then you have to
address bigger problems.

00:16:28.210 --> 00:16:33.810
There is no social well-being
or community well-being

00:16:33.810 --> 00:16:35.790
in the absence of
personal well-being,

00:16:35.790 --> 00:16:39.490
because we are units of society.

00:16:39.490 --> 00:16:42.180
So if we want to move in the
direction of some of the things

00:16:42.180 --> 00:16:47.880
that were mentioned
by Dr. Williams,

00:16:47.880 --> 00:16:50.840
if you want to move in the
direction of a more peaceful,

00:16:50.840 --> 00:16:54.000
just, sustainable,
healthier, and joyful world,

00:16:54.000 --> 00:16:57.840
then we have to look at what
creates for purpose-driven

00:16:57.840 --> 00:17:01.650
well-being, or what we
call career well-being,

00:17:01.650 --> 00:17:05.819
people who have happy
careers, who are on purpose,

00:17:05.819 --> 00:17:08.819
who are engaged with other
people who complement

00:17:08.819 --> 00:17:12.720
their strengths, who have shared
vision and are emotionally

00:17:12.720 --> 00:17:13.579
bonded--

00:17:13.579 --> 00:17:16.859
create for extremely
successful careers.

00:17:16.859 --> 00:17:22.230
Then, you have social and
emotional and community

00:17:22.230 --> 00:17:24.599
well-being, which
is, do you have

00:17:24.599 --> 00:17:29.550
a close group of family and
friends that you can rely on?

00:17:29.550 --> 00:17:32.160
Are you socially engaged?

00:17:32.160 --> 00:17:34.680
As far as communities
are concerned,

00:17:34.680 --> 00:17:39.450
do you offer some
service as a volunteer?

00:17:39.450 --> 00:17:42.870
Do you gather in a
community to envision

00:17:42.870 --> 00:17:44.920
the future of your community?

00:17:44.920 --> 00:17:48.690
Do you have some kind of
practice, spiritual practice

00:17:48.690 --> 00:17:50.430
that you do together?

00:17:50.430 --> 00:17:53.520
In India-- and I know people
are watching in India--

00:17:53.520 --> 00:17:57.840
we use these three words,
Seva, Satsang, and Simran.

00:17:57.840 --> 00:18:00.750
Seva means service.

00:18:00.750 --> 00:18:03.030
Satsang means a
gathering of people

00:18:03.030 --> 00:18:07.710
who are looking for ways to
improve well-being and search

00:18:07.710 --> 00:18:10.470
for what is called reality.

00:18:10.470 --> 00:18:15.270
And Simran is some kind of
contemplative self-inquiry.

00:18:15.270 --> 00:18:19.530
Those are the essence
of community well-being.

00:18:19.530 --> 00:18:22.110
Social well-being,
career well-being,

00:18:22.110 --> 00:18:24.150
community well-being,
and, ultimately,

00:18:24.150 --> 00:18:26.460
financial well-being are linked.

00:18:26.460 --> 00:18:28.080
Financial well-being
doesn't have

00:18:28.080 --> 00:18:32.310
to do with how much money you
make, but the security that you

00:18:32.310 --> 00:18:39.390
have if you have default ways of
ensuring that you will be fine

00:18:39.390 --> 00:18:42.810
if you fall sick, that you
have employment, that you have

00:18:42.810 --> 00:18:45.440
disability, that
you have insurance,

00:18:45.440 --> 00:18:50.850
and that you can look forward
to security as you get old.

00:18:50.850 --> 00:18:52.650
And finally, the
spiritual well-being,

00:18:52.650 --> 00:18:54.360
which is another topic--

00:18:54.360 --> 00:18:56.070
who are we?

00:18:56.070 --> 00:18:58.170
The hard problem
of consciousness--

00:18:58.170 --> 00:19:00.450
is consciousness a
byproduct of our brain,

00:19:00.450 --> 00:19:03.450
or is it more
fundamental in nature?

00:19:03.450 --> 00:19:06.570
Is consciousness the
source of all experience?

00:19:06.570 --> 00:19:12.000
And that's what I'm focusing
my work on now totally, looking

00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:14.040
at the hard problem
of consciousness

00:19:14.040 --> 00:19:17.310
and understanding
our consciousness

00:19:17.310 --> 00:19:23.500
both personal and collective as
a source of insight, intuition,

00:19:23.500 --> 00:19:29.040
imagination, creativity,
vision, higher purpose,

00:19:29.040 --> 00:19:31.830
and the power of intention.

00:19:31.830 --> 00:19:34.110
So when we look at well-being--
and it's measurable.

00:19:34.110 --> 00:19:37.770
Everything I've said is
measurable-- social well-being,

00:19:37.770 --> 00:19:40.110
community well-being,
financial well-being,

00:19:40.110 --> 00:19:42.870
physical well-being,
emotional well-being.

00:19:42.870 --> 00:19:48.030
In fact, now, in addition to
doing perceived stress scores,

00:19:48.030 --> 00:19:52.590
we're also doing spiritual
well-being stress scores called

00:19:52.590 --> 00:19:58.660
understanding your relationship
with the ecosystem at large--

00:19:58.660 --> 00:20:02.670
not just the social
ecosystem, but our connection

00:20:02.670 --> 00:20:06.810
to nature and, ultimately, our
connection to the universe.

00:20:06.810 --> 00:20:09.480
It's a big topic.

00:20:09.480 --> 00:20:12.330
Public health should be
the number one discipline

00:20:12.330 --> 00:20:18.540
for anyone wanting to go into
the future of well-being,

00:20:18.540 --> 00:20:21.060
because it's going
to be predictable.

00:20:21.060 --> 00:20:22.860
It's going to be precise.

00:20:22.860 --> 00:20:27.520
It's going to be
preventable, in many cases.

00:20:27.520 --> 00:20:31.560
It's going to be
participatory, and it's

00:20:31.560 --> 00:20:34.170
going to be processed-oriented.

00:20:34.170 --> 00:20:38.370
And it's going to require more
than academic institutions.

00:20:38.370 --> 00:20:44.790
It's going to require a
global public awareness

00:20:44.790 --> 00:20:50.910
and require a global
action plan, which

00:20:50.910 --> 00:20:54.780
I think is feasible
through blockchain

00:20:54.780 --> 00:20:59.010
technologies and
other social networks,

00:20:59.010 --> 00:21:05.100
so that we can collectively not
only envision but practically

00:21:05.100 --> 00:21:09.120
embark in the direction
of a more peaceful, just,

00:21:09.120 --> 00:21:12.940
sustainable, healthier,
and joyful world.

00:21:12.940 --> 00:21:15.520
I was sharing with Michelle
some of our research

00:21:15.520 --> 00:21:19.980
now at the Chopra Foundation
through meta-analysis

00:21:19.980 --> 00:21:21.330
of big data.

00:21:21.330 --> 00:21:26.500
It seems the number one epidemic
of our civilization is stress,

00:21:26.500 --> 00:21:30.210
but it's also connected
directly or indirectly

00:21:30.210 --> 00:21:31.920
to almost every
illness that you can

00:21:31.920 --> 00:21:35.730
think of and even to social
violence and conflict.

00:21:35.730 --> 00:21:39.960
And ultimately,
even climate change

00:21:39.960 --> 00:21:42.970
can all be linked to
our collective behavior.

00:21:42.970 --> 00:21:47.280
It's time to take
schools of public health

00:21:47.280 --> 00:21:51.480
with leadership such
as this here at Harvard

00:21:51.480 --> 00:21:55.410
School of Public Health,
come together collectively,

00:21:55.410 --> 00:21:59.280
and bring about a
shift in well-being.

00:21:59.280 --> 00:22:01.070
And I'll just end there.

00:22:01.070 --> 00:22:02.820
Well-being is more
than wellness.

00:22:02.820 --> 00:22:05.880
Wellness is having a
good cholesterol level

00:22:05.880 --> 00:22:07.860
and good blood pressure.

00:22:07.860 --> 00:22:12.660
But well-being is a
state of consciousness

00:22:12.660 --> 00:22:16.530
where you measure the
quality of your life in all

00:22:16.530 --> 00:22:19.270
the different buckets that
I've mentioned-- physical,

00:22:19.270 --> 00:22:25.210
emotional, spiritual, community,
social, financial, and career.

00:22:25.210 --> 00:22:25.710
Thank you.

